(secondQuint)Study to Evaluate the Efficacy of Octenisept in Patients With Chronic Wounds.

 Randomized, double-blind, placebo-controlled trial with octenisept(R) or placebo in patients with chronic leg ulcers.

 The study will be conducted at a single center with a total of 70 patients.

 Patients will be randomized to either the octenisept(R) group or to the placebo group.

 Primary Objectives: Antimicrobial efficacy of octenisept(R) compared to placebo.

 Secondary Objectives: Subjective tolerance of octenisept(R), evaluation of wound parameters.

